gomodel:SYNGO_5261  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Figure 1d: confocal imaging of immunofluorescence labeling for SRPX2, VGLUT1 and PSD95 (DLG4) in cultured cortical neurons showed partial overlap. Imaging resolution is too low to discern subcellular localization as pre- and/or post-synaptic.\n\nFigure 1e: synaptic fractions showed SRPX2 enriched in P2 and synaptosomes as compared to homogenate and P1 fractions.. Experimental description: Results, Figure 1 legend: \"DIV 21 dissociated rat cortical neurons were surface-stained for SRPX2 and then permeabilized and stained for excitatory and inhibitory synaptic markers.\"\n\nantibody:\n\"The SRPX2 polyclonal antibody was generated by injecting rabbits with the C- terminal 16 amino acids of rat SRPX2 protein conjugated to keyhole limpet hemocyanin. The antibody was then affinity-purified, and its specificity was verified by lack of reactivity with SRPX and decreased reactivity in SRPX2 knockdown cultures (data not shown)\"" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-4973-5732" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" ;
        dc:date           "2023-03-09" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_5261" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

